This paper discusses the design and analysis of replication algorithms for distributed hash tables, which are commonly used in distributed computing and networking. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also deals with data storage and maintenance, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The reliability analysis and fault tolerance aspects of the replication algorithms suggest a possible fit with cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the impact of replica placement strategies on performance and reliability, which could be relevant to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper mentions the need for security and privacy in distributed systems, which could relate to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
